#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Calc is the &libo; spreadsheet module. Spreadsheets consist of several "
"sheets, containing cells which can be filled with elements like text, "
"numbers, or formulas. A formula can manipulate data from other cells to "
"generate a value for the cell in which it is inserted. Calc also allows you "
"to define ranges, filter and sort data and creates charts from data to "
"present it graphically. Using pivot tables, you can combine, analyze or "
"compare larger amounts of data."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This chapter can only introduce some very basic Calc functionality. For more "
"information and for complete instructions, see the &libo; application help "
"and the sources listed in <xref linkend=\"sec.oo.oview.help\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "VBA Macros"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Calc can process many VBA macros in Excel documents. However, support for "
"VBA macros is not complete. When opening an Excel spreadsheet that makes "
"heavy use of macros, you might discover that some do not work."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a New Document"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:40
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are two ways to create a new Calc document:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "From Scratch"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:48
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a new empty document, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>New</guimenu> <guimenu>Spreadsheet</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:57
#, no-c-format
msgid "From a Template"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use a template, click <menuchoice> <guimenu>File</guimenu> <guimenu>New</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Templates</guimenu> </menuchoice> and open, for example, "
"<guimenu>Finances</guimenu>. From the list of spreadsheet templates, select "
"the one that fits your needs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Access the individual sheets by clicking their respective tabs at the bottom "
"of the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Enter data in the cells as desired. To adjust the appearance, either use the "
"<guimenu>Formatting</guimenu> toolbar or side bar panel, or use the "
"<guimenu>Format</guimenu> menu&mdash;or define styles as described in <xref "
"linkend=\"sec.oo.calc.styles\"/>. Use the <guimenu>File</guimenu> menu or "
"the relevant buttons in the toolbar to print and save your document."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:83
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Formatting and Styles in Calc"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:85
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Calc comes with a few built-in cell and page styles to improve the "
"appearance of your spreadsheets and reports. Although these built-in styles "
"are adequate for many uses, you will probably find it useful to create "
"styles for your own frequently used formatting preferences."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:93
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Style"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Format</guimenu> <guimenu>Styles</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Styles and Formatting</guimenu> </menuchoice> or press <keycap>F11</"
"keycap>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:102 apps_librecalc.xml:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the top of the panel <guimenu>Styles and Formatting</guimenu>, click "
"either <guimenu>Cell Styles</guimenu> (a green cell) or <guimenu>Page "
"Styles</guimenu> (a document)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:109
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right-click anywhere in the list of styles in the panel <guimenu>Styles and "
"Formatting</guimenu>. Then click <guimenu>New</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:115
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify a name for the style and use the various tabs to set the desired "
"formatting options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:121 apps_librecalc.xml:154
#, no-c-format
msgid "When you are done configuring the style, click <guimenu>OK</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "Modifying a Style"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:130
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <menuchoice> <guimenu>Format</guimenu> <guimenu>Styles</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Styles and Formatting</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right-click the name of the style you want to change, then click "
"<guimenu>Modify</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Change the desired formatting options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:160
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To apply a style to specific cells, select the cells you want to format. "
"Then double-click the style you want to apply in the <guimenu>Styles and "
"Formatting</guimenu> window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "Working With Sheets"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Sheets are a good method to organize your calculations. For example, if you "
"have a business, accounting might be much clearer if you create a sheet for "
"each month."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To insert a new sheet after the last sheet, click the button <guimenu>+</"
"guimenu> next to the sheet tabs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To insert one or more new sheet in your spreadsheet from a file or at a "
"specific position at once, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:186
#, no-c-format
msgid "Inserting New Sheets"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Right-click a sheet tab and select <guimenu>Insert Sheet</guimenu>. A dialog "
"opens."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Decide whether the new sheet should be positioned before or after the "
"selected sheet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:200
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a new sheet, make sure the <guimenu>New Sheet</guimenu> radio "
"button is activated. Enter the number of sheets and the sheet name. Skip the "
"rest of this step."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "Alternatively, to import a sheet from another file, do the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <guimenu>From file</guimenu> and click <guimenu>Browse</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the file name and confirm with <guimenu>OK</guimenu>. All the sheet "
"names are now displayed in the list."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the sheet names you want to import by holding the <keycap function="
"\"shift\"></keycap> key and clicking them."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add the sheet or sheets, confirm with <guimenu>OK</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To rename a sheet, right-click the tab of the sheet and select "
"<guimenu>Rename Sheet</guimenu>. Alternatively, you can also double-click "
"the sheet tab."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To delete one or multiple sheets, do the following: Select the sheet you "
"want to delete. To select more than one sheet, hold down <keycap function="
"\"shift\"></keycap> while making the selection. Then right-click the tab of "
"the sheet, choose <guimenu>Delete Sheet</guimenu> and confirm with "
"<guimenu>Yes</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:250
#, no-c-format
msgid "Conditional Formatting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Conditional formatting is a useful feature to highlight certain values in "
"your spreadsheet. For example, define a condition and if the condition is "
"<literal>true</literal>, a style is applied to each cell that fulfills this "
"condition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable AutoCalculate"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before you apply conditional formatting, choose <menuchoice> <guimenu>Tools</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Cell Contents</guimenu> <guimenu>AutoCalculate</guimenu> </"
"menuchoice>. You should see a check mark in front of <guimenu>AutoCalculate</"
"guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:270
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using Conditional Formatting"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Define a style first. This style is applied to each cell when your condition "
"is <literal>true</literal>. Use <menuchoice> <guimenu>Format</"
"guimenu><guimenu>Styles and Formatting</guimenu> </menuchoice> or press "
"<keycap>F11</keycap>. For more information, see <xref linkend=\"pro.oo.calc."
"createstyle\"/>. Confirm with <guimenu>OK</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select the cell range where you want to apply your condition."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:287
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Format</guimenu> <guimenu>Conditional "
"Formatting</guimenu> <guimenu>Condition</guimenu> </menuchoice> from the "
"menu. A dialog opens."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:294
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You now see a template for a new condition. Conditions can operate in "
"multiple modes:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: apps_librecalc.xml:300
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cell value is"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The condition tests if a cell matches a certain value. Next to the first "
"drop-down box, select an operator such as <guimenu>equal to</guimenu>, "
"<guimenu>less than</guimenu>, or <guimenu>greater than</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: apps_librecalc.xml:312
#, no-c-format
msgid "Formula is"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:315
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The condition tests if a certain formula returns <literal>true</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: apps_librecalc.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid "Date is"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:325
#, no-c-format
msgid "The condition tests if a certain date value is reached."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: apps_librecalc.xml:331
#, no-c-format
msgid "All Cells"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:334
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This mode allows creating data visualizations that depend on the value of a "
"cell, similarly to <guimenu>Cell value is</guimenu>. However, with "
"<guimenu>All Cells</guimenu>, you can use one condition to apply an entire "
"range of styles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The types of styles that can be used are color scales (cell background "
"color), data bars (bars with changing width in the cell) and icon sets (an "
"icon in the cell)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:345
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For example, a color scale allows assigning <literal>0</literal> a black "
"background and <literal>100</literal> a green background. All values in "
"between are calculated automatically. For example, <literal>50</literal> "
"receives a dark green background."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:356
#, no-c-format
msgid "For this example, keep the default: <guimenu>Cell value is</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:361
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select an operator and the value of the cell you want to test for."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:366
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Choose the style you want to apply when this condition is <literal>true</"
"literal> or click <guimenu>New Style</guimenu> to define a new appearance."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:373
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you need additional conditions, click <guimenu>Add</guimenu>. Then repeat "
"the previous steps."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Confirm with <guimenu>OK</guimenu>. Now the style of your cells has changed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: remark
#: apps_librecalc.xml:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We might also want a procedure showing how to use the Manage dialog to "
"remove conditions. -- sknorr, 2015-09-17"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:392
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grouping and Ungrouping Cells"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Grouping a cell range allows hiding parts of a spreadsheet. This makes "
"spreadsheets more readable, as you can hide all the parts you are not "
"currently interested in. It is possible to group rows or columns and nest "
"groups in other groups."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "To group a range, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grouping a Selected Cell Range"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:408
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select a cell range in your spreadsheet."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Data</guimenu> <guimenu>Group and Outline</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Group</guimenu> </menuchoice>. A dialog appears."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:420
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Decide if you want to group your selected range by rows or by columns. "
"Confirm with <guimenu>OK</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After grouping selected cells, a line indicating the grouped cell range "
"appears in the upper-left margin. Fold or unfold the cell range with the "
"<guimenu>+</guimenu> and <guimenu>–</guimenu> icons. The numbers at the top "
"left of the margins display the depth of your groups and can be clicked too."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:434
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To ungroup a cell range, click into a cell which belongs to a group and "
"select <menuchoice> <guimenu>Data</guimenu> <guimenu>Group and Outline</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Ungroup</guimenu> </menuchoice>. The line in the margin "
"disappears. The innermost group is always deleted first."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:442
#, no-c-format
msgid "Freezing Rows or Columns as Headers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:444
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have a spreadsheet with lots of data, scrolling usually makes the "
"header disappear. &libo; can lock rows or columns or both, so they remain "
"fixed as you scroll around."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:450
#, no-c-format
msgid "To freeze a single row or a single column, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Freezing a Single Row or Column"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:457
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a frozen area before a row, click the header of the row "
"(<literal>1</literal>, <literal>2</literal>, <literal>3</literal>, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Alternatively, to create a frozen area above a column, click the header of "
"the column (<literal>A</literal>, <literal>B</literal>, <literal>C</"
"literal>, ...)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenu>Freeze Rows and "
"Columns</guimenu> </menuchoice>. A dark line appears, indicating the frozen "
"area."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:476
#, no-c-format
msgid "It is also possible to freeze both rows and columns:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: apps_librecalc.xml:481
#, no-c-format
msgid "Freezing Row and Column"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click into the cell to the right of the column and below the row you want "
"frozen. For example, if your header occupies the space from A1 to B3, click "
"cell C4."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select <menuchoice> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenu>Freeze Rows and "
"Columns</guimenu></menuchoice>. A dark line appears, indicating which area "
"is frozen."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apps_librecalc.xml:498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To unfreeze, select <menuchoice><guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenu>Freeze Rows "
"and Columns</guimenu></menuchoice>. The check mark before the menu item "
"disappears."
msgstr ""
